  "texts": [
    "The present work expands on the data-driven literature summarized above by proposing a space-time deep-learning model based on an Ensemble Neural Network (ENN) architecture.",
    "Neural Networks (NN) are not new to the landslide literature, although they have found the spotlight so far mostly for automated landslide detection (Catani, 2021; Meena et al., 2022), monitoring (Neaupane and Achet, 2004; Wang et al., 2005), and for landslide susceptibility assessment (Lee et al., 2004; Catani et al., 2005; Gomez and Kavzoglu, 2005; Grelle et al., 2014; Montrasio et al., 2014; Catani et al., 2016; Nocentini et al., 2023).",
    "Here, the main difference is that our ENN is built as an ensemble made of two elements, i.e., a landslide susceptibility classifier and a landslide density area regression model, both simultaneously defined over the same spatio-temporal domain.",
    "Thanks to the open data repository of Kincey et al. (2021), we tested our space-time ENN, fully complying for the first time with the landslide hazard definition (as per Guzzetti et al., 1999).",
    "The paper is organized as follows: Sect. 2 describes the data we used; Sect."
